uima.cas.Sofa.sofaString: The aorta remains tortuous. The pulmonary vasculature is not engorged. Lungs are hyperinflated. Apart from minimal atelectasis in the lung bases and biapical scarring in the lung apices, more pronounced on the right, the lungs are clear.No pleural effusion or pneumothorax is demonstrated.
